name: Reebok Ragnar Niagara
intro:
Reebok Ragnar Niagara is back! On May 19-20th, you and your team of 12 members (or 6-member ultra team) can experience the best parts of Ontario by foot, including the majestic beauty of Niagara Falls! This overnight relay kicks off in the quaint town of Cobourg. From there, you and your team will run relay-style next to the Canadian shores of Lake Ontario on the Waterfront Trail. This area is renowned for its gorgeous vineyards and unspoiled beauty. As the sun falls into the horizon, you’ll run through the night and take in the Toronto skyline and stars overhead. After you cross the finish line as a team, relax and peer at the U.S. from the sight where 150,000 gallons of water flow each second. Mystery, adventure and stunning beauty has drawn sightseers from around the globe to witness the famous falls.

Don’t miss out on your chance to experience a one-of-a-kind cultural experience: friendly Canucks, eclectic Ragnarians, natural beauty and famous landmarks. Add Reebok Ragnar Niagara to your running calendar!

GREAT NEWS! All 2017 Reebok Ragnar Relay captains will be receiving a free pair of Reebok running shoes!! As a captain, we know you are committed to going the distance and Reebok wants your feedback. Check out our Reebok Shoes page for more info!
charity:
Ragnar is proud to partner with The Princess Margaret Cancer Foundation for Reebok Ragnar Niagara.

PMCF Mission:  To raise and steward funds to deliver breakthrough research, exemplary teaching, and compassionate care at The Princess Margaret, one of the top 5 cancer research centres in the world.

For information about becoming a PMCF fundraising team, please contact Keith Clarke Keith.Clarke@thepmcf.ca
